-- Greece Sells 750,000 Spot Carbon Permits at 5.78 Euros a Ton
-- B y   A l e s s a n d r o   V i t e l l i
-- 2012-12-05T15:52:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-05/greece-sells-750-000-spot-carbon-permits-at-5-78-euros-a-ton.html
Greece  sold 750,000 European Union
carbon permits at 5.78 euros ($7.56) a metric ton in an auction,
according to the Athens exchange.  Bids totaled 2.1 million tons, or 2.8 times the amount on
offer, Alexandra Grispou, a spokeswoman for the exchange, said
in an e-mailed statement. The nation will not hold any further
carbon permit sales this year, Grispou said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandro Vitelli in Doha at 
 avitelli1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
